== Duck Fat Mashed Potatoes ==

Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces
(for a smoother texture, peel potatoes first). Place in a large #pot with half
the @Thyme{¼%ounce} sprigs and enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring
to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove and discard thyme
sprigs. Reserve ¼ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to
pot.

== Duck a l'Orange ==

Meanwhile, pat @Duck Breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels; season all over
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place skin sides down in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan. Cook over medium heat until skin is crisp, carefully reserving
fat in a small #bowl as it renders, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat if skin browns too quickly.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}; toss in a separate small
bowl with half the @Red Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a big
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Zest @Orange{1} until you have 1 tsp; halve orange. Squeeze juice from 1 half
into a third small bowl. Peel remaining half, then dice orange into ½-inch
pieces.

> For 4 servings, squeeze juice from 2 halves; peel and dice remaining orange.

To bowl with juice, stir in @Apricot Jam{2%tablespoon}, @Chicken Stock
Concentrate{1}, half the orange zest, and remaining vinegar. Pick thyme leaves
from remaining sprigs until you have 1 tsp; roughly chop leaves.

Once skin is crisp, flip over duck in pan and cook to desired doneness,
~{3-5%minutes} more. Transfer to a #cutting board to rest. Add chopped thyme to
same pan over medium heat and cook until fragrant, ~{30 seconds} to ~{1%minute}.
Stir in orange juice mixture and bring to a simmer. Cook until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted; turn off heat.

== Duck Fat Mashed Potatoes (cont.) ==

Heat pot with drained potatoes over medium-low. Add @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}
and @Butter{1%tablespoon}; mash with a #potato masher{}, adding up to ¼ cup
potato cooking liquid, as necessary, until smooth. Stir in reserved duck fat,
to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

> 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

== Arugula-Almond Salad ==

In a large #bowl, combine pickling liquid from shallot, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon},
a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, remaining orange zest, and a pinch
of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss with @Arugula{2%ounce}, shallot, orange pieces,
and @Almonds{1%ounce}(toasted). Season with salt and pepper to taste. Slice duck
crosswise. Divide between plates with salad and potatoes. Spoon glaze over duck.